strings: <voice_0x010014F3><se_low>King Trode: His fever appears to have abated, my dear.
<voice_0x010014F4><se_low>King Trode: And the physician was sure the lad is out of danger now. He should be fine.
<voice_0x010014F5><se_low>King Trode: So, I think perhaps it's time you got some rest, hm?

<voice_0x010014F6><se_low>King Trode: You must look after yourself, my dear.
I'm told you haven't been eating well
since your mother's passing.
<voice_0x010014F7><se_high>Princess Medea: No, Father, I'm quite all right.
<voice_0x010014F8><se_high>Princess Medea: I would like to stay here...just until he wakes up.

<voice_0x010014F9><se_low>King Trode: Hmph, well, if you insist. But have a care,
my child. You are in danger of making yourself ill like this.
<voice_0x010014FA><se_low>King Trode: Truly, that young lad has the luck of the devil. Had you not found him when you did, I daren't think what would have become of him.
<voice_0x010014FE><se_high>Princess Medea: Don't worry, you're going to be just fine.
